movie_title: Star Wars: Episode I - The Phantom Menace
title: a brief evaluation
review: There is no force collision, no lightsaber duel, and no bloodletting between father and son. There is plenty of cruelty and heroism in the war. The sincere friendship of the players, and the spirit of never giving up! This is the real suicide squad!

movie_title: Star Wars: Episode II - Attack of the Clones
title: a brief evaluation
review:
This is a classic in the minds of the American people, said to ignite the dream of countless people.
But for my age and cultural background, it is difficult to have a dream ignited by it.
It was one of the most imaginative films of decades past, and countless directors and people were so excited about the world it created that they couldn't help themselves.
But after so many years, the rich imagination and the advanced technology at that time seem to be no better than today.

movie_title: Star Wars: Episode VIII - The Last Jedi
title: a brief evaluation
review: Star Wars: episode viii, while bringing to an end the legacy of the old jedi, successfully launched a new generation of jedi stories. Although the movie is not perfect, the next development is still worth your and mine.
